Nigerian President  Goodluck Jonathan 
proposed a continent-wide tax on commodities in  Africa  to help
fund investment in infrastructure.  Africa needs to coordinate on its tax policies, Jonathan
told an African Union conference in  Equatorial Guinea  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
